  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: The Great And Venerable Teacher
---
\"Impossible!" said Hsu Yu. "Eyes that are blind have no way to tell the
loveliness of faces and features; eyes with no pupils have no way to
tell the beauty of colored and embroidered silks."
